title: Have you seen a search result from Google disappear that is not deleted? - Quora

response.answer_text: G morning, First allow me to say that I have seen all kinds of things, more so now, with all the big boys working with skeleton crews. Am amazed the internet is still up and running, the only reason why that is so, is so people don’t go crazy coping with covid… in a nutshell. Need to keep the masses entertained somehow. Now… With that out of the way, would of been nice to know if you are referring to a search result on first page on G? that is no longer there? that is normal. Other posts become more relevant with more authority and the one you saw in first page is now on 2nd, 5th… you get my drift. So it did not disappeared is just no longer in the place it was. Everyday normal. If you are referring to a search result no matter in what position? Yes still possible but that can be a number of factors about that specific post that G “hides” and the reasons can be endless. Which to be honest way to early for me to name them all and am sure will forget a few, for that you can read G terms and conditions for posts and how they get ranked so on and so forth. Hope I answered it, coffee barely kicking in. If not hope there are more answers already with better info or same, which ever the case? Wish you a great day!
